 
 ------------------------HAMS-MREL (Hydrodynamic Analysis of Marine Structures - Marine Renewable Energies Lab)---------------------
 
                                                         Code Author for the multi-body formulations and implementations: Vaibhav Raghavan
 
                                                         Code Author for the single-body formulation: Yingyi Liu
 
  HAMS-MREL is an open-source software for computing wave diffraction and radiation of 3D structures.
 
 Please cite the following papers in your publications, reports, etc., when HAMS-MREL has been used in your work:
 
  (1) Raghavan, V., Loukogeorgaki, E., Mantadakis, N., Metrikine, A. V., & Lavidas, G. (2024).
      HAMS‑MREL, a new open‑source multiple body solver for marine renewable energies: Model description,
      application and validation. Renewable Energy, 237, 127857. DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.renene.2024.121577
 
  (2) Raghavan, V., Metrikine, A.V. & Lavidas, G. Theory and validation of the new features in BIEM solver HAMS-MREL.
      J. Ocean Eng. Mar. Energy 12, 53–71 (2026). DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/s40722-025-00431-8
 
